  "prompt": "What is the most used word in Malayalam?",
  "response": "Determining the **most used word** in Malayalam can depend on the context\u2014whether it's spoken language, written text, or literature. However, one of the most frequently used words in everyday Malayalam is **\"\u0d05\u0d24\u0d4d\" (\"athu\")**, which means **\"that\"** or **\"it\"**. It is a versatile word used in various contexts and sentences.  \n\nOther commonly used words include:  \n- **\"\u0d1e\u0d3e\u0d7b\" (\"nj\u0101\u1e47\")** \u2013 \"I\"  \n- **\"\u0d28\u0d40\" (\"n\u012b\")** \u2013 \"you\"  \n- **\"\u0d07\u0d24\u0d4d\" (\"ithu\")** \u2013 \"this\"  \n- **\"\u0d09\u0d23\u0d4d\u0d1f\u0d4d\" (\"u\u1e47\u1e6d\")** \u2013 \"is\" or \"exists\"  \n\nIn terms of spoken language, particles like **\"-\u0d06\u0d23\u0d4d\" (\"-\u0101\u1e47\")** (a form of \"is\") and **\"-\u0d09\u0d02\" (\"-um\")** (meaning \"and\") are also extremely common.  \n\nThe frequency can vary based on the dataset or context analyzed, but **\"\u0d05\u0d24\u0d4d\"** is a strong candidate for the most used word in Malayalam.",
